          <gmd19157:processStep>
            <gmd19157:LI_ProcessStep>
              <gmd19157:description>
                <gco:CharacterString>The inversion corresponds to the results described in Piao et al. (2009). It is based on a “matrix” formulation (see Peylin et al., 2005).
Fluxes: solved at the spatial resolution of the transport model and monthly resolution; prior land fluxes taken as the climatology over 1996-2004 from the ORCHIDEE model (Krinner et al., 2005); prior ocean fluxes from Takahashi et al., (2002).
Prior land/ocean errors set to 6.0/2.5 Pg C yr-1 globally and spatially distributed according to the Gross Primary Production of ORCHIDEE / the surface area of ocean grid cells; flux error correlations between land/ocean grid-points, following an e-folding length of 1000/2000 km.
Observations: 73 sites from GLOBALVIEW-CO2 and CARBOEUROPE EU-project (9 sites); Errors (measurements + model) range between 0.4 ppm for remote stations (South Pole) and 3 ppm for continental sites (Hungaria).
Prescribed fluxes: fossil fuel with spatial distribution from Oliver and Berdowski (2001) and annual totals rescaled each year for each country using CDIAC statistics; Biomass burning from van der Werf et al. (2006).</gco:CharacterString>
              </gmd19157:description>
            </gmd19157:LI_ProcessStep>
          </gmd19157:processStep>
        </gmd19157:LI_Lineage>
